column37:
B means basics for being an attackman, but these are to be used sparingly.  
F means that these drills are foundational to the development of a great Attackman and should be used most.
S means the drills can be useful to Attackman, but are more supplementary.
N/A means that they do not apply to Attack, but can be done for fun.
X - These are advanced drills to try that can be done for fun.
column38:
This is the progression of the drill that corresponds to the category.  
Technique = a technique drill that breaks down an aspect of a drill and should be run before the drill elements.
Drill - Drills are exercises that use the techniques.
column39:
B means basics for being an Midfielder, but these are to be used sparingly.  
F means that these drills are foundational to the development of a great Midfielder and should be used most
S means the drills can be useful to Midfielder, but are more supplementary.
N/A means that they do not apply to midfield, but can be done for fun.
X - These are advanced drills to try that can be done for fun.
column40:
